        <svcproc svcproctype="TSI" graphiccount="3">
            <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
            <svcsubproc>
                <title>Subject 1:</title>
                <para>A new water pump configuration is released for T 444E engines starting with serial No. 58559 and
                    above. The water pump now incorporates the water inlet and coolant filter header. A new pump bearing
                    is also released.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <important>
                        <para>Early Style Water Pump
                            <emph type="italic">With Aluminum Housing</emph>
                            Will Continue To Be Furnished On Service Engine Assemblies Nos. Above 58558:
                        </para>
                        <randlist type="bullet">
                            <item>
                                <para>1994 MY Service Engine 1 823 489 C91 w/o Exhaust Back Press. Device</para>
                            </item>
                            <item>
                                <para>1994 MY Service Engine 1 823 488 C91, w/Exhaust Back Press. Device</para>
                            </item>
                            <item>
                                <para>1995 MY Service Engine 1 823 619 C91, w/o Exhaust Back Press. Device</para>
                            </item>
                            <item>
                                <para>1995 MY Service Engine 1 823 620 C91, w/Exhaust Back Press. Device</para>
                            </item>
                        </randlist>
                    </important>
                </specpara>
                <para>The new water pump is serviced in a package with the mounting gasket
                    <emph type="bold">(Package P/N 1 823 669 C91).</emph>
                    Pump mounting hardware and coolant filter are not included in the package. The new pump uses
                    different length hardware (See
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9512141">Figure 1.</hotlnk>
                    for bolt location. For part Nos. see "Parts Affected" at the end of this service letter).
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Coolant Filter
                            <emph type="bold">(P/N 1 822 627 C1)</emph>
                            Did Not Change.
                        </para>
                        <para>Water Pump Assembly Component Parts Are Not Serviced Separately, Except Plugs, Coolant
                            Filter Shut-off Valve, Valve O-Ring and Retaining Ring (See "Parts Affected").
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <para>The new water inlet is an integral part of the pump body and is relocated to the RH-side, whereas
                    the previous inlet was mounted on the LH-side. The new coolant filter header is an integral part of
                    the pump body also, and is now located on the LH-side. The former header was mounted to the
                    crankcase, beneath the oil cooler (Refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9512141">Figure 1</hotlnk>
                    and
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9512142">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <para>The new design of the water pump eliminates the need for remote coolant filter piping. The coolant
                    now flows directly to the filter from the water pump. A new coolant shut-off valve is easily
                    accessed at the front of the water pump (See
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9512141">Figure 1.</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <important>
                        <para>Be sure after servicing coolant filter that the shut-off valve lever is in the "open"
                            position see
                            <hotlnk xrefid="f9512141">Figure 1.</hotlnk>
                        </para>
                    </important>
                </specpara>
                <para>Idler pulleys, hardware, belts and belt tensioner are changed to provide components compatible
                    with the new water pump (See "Parts Affected"). Also, refer to Parts Information Letter (P.I.L.
                    94-08-51).
                </para>
            </svcsubproc>
            <svcsubproc>
                <title>Subject 2:</title>
                <para>The cast iron water pump can be installed on earlier engines (Below eng. serial No. 58559) with
                    the use of retrofit kit,
                    <emph type="bold">P/N 1 698 417 C91</emph>, clamp,
                    <emph type="bold">P/N 1 673 815 C1</emph>
                    and a water pump kit,
                    <emph type="bold">P/N 1 823 669 C91</emph>, along with the necessary mounting bolts (see "Parts
                    Affected"). This retrofit kit,
                    <emph type="bold">P/N 1 698 417 C91</emph>, consists of a formed hose,
                    <emph type="bold">P/N 1 697 761 C1</emph>, a formed pipe,
                    <emph type="bold">P/N 1 697 744 C1</emph>, and plugs.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>
                            <emph type="underscr">INSTALLATION OF THE CAST IRON WATER PUMP RETROFIT KIT UTILIZES THE
                                ORIGINAL BELT, PULLEY, HOSES AND RADIATOR.
                            </emph>
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <para>The original lower hose MUST BE reoriented downward and inboard 65 degrees (Refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9512143">Figure 3</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <para>The new crossover pipe,
                    <emph type="bold">P/N 1 697 744 C1,</emph>
                    MUST BE supported off the crossmember using clamp,
                    <emph type="bold">P/N 1 673 815 C1</emph>
                    (Refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9512143">Figure 3</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <para>Rerouting surge hoses may be necessary on some installations. (See
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9512141">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <para>The original coolant filter mounting header and pipes MUST BE REMOVED AND THE OPEN PORTS PLUGGED.
                    The coolant filter,
                    <emph type="bold">P/N 1 822 627 C1,</emph>
                    did not change. Use of a new filter is recommended according to the Scheduled Maintenance Chart
                    listed in the engine operation and maintenance manual.
                </para>
